#lectureNotes 
Turing Machine

Not limited in memory size

One Input tape of infinite length

K work tapes of infinite length

One output tape of infinite length

One State box of  states![](data:image/png;base64,)

Each tape has a read head

Work and output tapes have write head capability

Q is for state

Sigma is input tape

Delta: Q * Sigma^k+1 -> Q*Sigma^k*{L,R,…}^K+1

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Delta is a transition table of each state and each input

Turing machine is not a computer, but a single algorithm simulation -- Defined by the delta function of transition

Universal Turing Machine
